<p>Seems the original version did not save this important paragraph so I have added it:</p>
<p>On 15 September 2010 The New York Sun reports <a href="http://www.nysun.com/editorials/greenspans-warning-on-gold/87080" rel="nofollow">Alan Greenspan spoke at the Council on Foreign Relations</a> and in response to a question about why gold was hitting new highs he said, &#8220;“Fiat money has no place to go but gold. &#8230; If all currencies are moving up or down together, the question is: relative to what? Gold is the canary in the coal mine. It signals problems with respect to currency markets. Central banks should pay attention to it.”</p>
